      "widgets_values": [
        "ATLAS INPAINT LAYERS II — sci-fi hangar, THREE depth bands (detailed example; partial: in-repo Atlas nodes only)\n\nExtends atlas_camera_inpaint_layers_workflow.json (the 2-band Monument Valley intro) with:\n  • THREE clean-plate layers — bg (near_pct 0.65 → +inf), mid (0.20 → 0.65), fg (0 → 0.20) — chained bg → mid → fg so all three land on one solve as separate ProjectionSources (priority fg 10 > mid 5 > bg 0; nearer band wins where they overlap).\n  • AtlasDepthLayerMask for BOTH occluded bands (bg + mid), with their occlusion_masks previewed via MaskToImage → PreviewImage so you can see exactly what each band's inpaint pass would need to fill. The fg band needs no mask/inpaint — nothing occludes the frontmost layer.\n  • A detached AtlasViewportControls Output Desk wired into the viewport's controls + output_profile inputs — moves every toolbar/panel (primitives, 📽/📊/ℹ, 🎥 Camera Path, 💡 Lights tab, Render Passes) off the viewport node, leaving it render-only.\n  • AtlasExportSolveJSON at the end — the exported solve carries all three clean-plate ProjectionSources.\n\nBand percentiles are per-photo tuning knobs: for this hangar the fg band catches the nearest deck plating, mid catches the parked ship, bg catches the far wall/ceiling. Nudge near_pct/far_pct pairs (they MUST stay identical between each AtlasDepthLayerMask and its matching AtlasCleanPlateLayer — both call the same _resolve_depth_band helper).\n\nTUNING NOTE (calibrated live on this image, 3 iterations): band-clipped relief meshes tear at their band boundaries IN ADDITION to normal silhouette tearing, so per-layer meshes want a finer grid and a more tolerant edge threshold than a single whole-frame mesh — relief_grid 384 + depth_edge_rel 1.5 here vs the 128/0.5 defaults (at 128/0.5 the ship region was mostly holes; the higher edge tolerance is safe within a band because the band clip already bounds each mesh's depth range). Also pick band edges that do NOT slice through your subject: 0.30/0.60 cut this ship in half across bands; 0.20/0.65 keeps it whole in mid.\n\nThe external inpaint step (Acly/comfyui-inpaint-nodes, GPL-3.0) is a documented placeholder — see the note in group ③.\n\n2026-07-07 viewport upgrade: the Atlas viewport now runs on a vendored three.js r185 bundle (atlas_camera/comfy/web/lib/atlas-three.bundle.js) instead of a CDN — works fully offline, and the 🧍 Woman / 🚗 Sedan scale-proxy models and 📥 FBX camera import (previously silently broken by an unresolvable CDN import) now work."
      ]
    },
