      "widgets_values": [
        "EXTERNAL INPAINT STEP (not included — needs Acly/comfyui-inpaint-nodes, GPL-3.0):\n\nThe links feeding the BG and MID AtlasCleanPlateLayer plate_image inputs are PLACEHOLDERS — they reuse the original LoadImage output directly so this graph stays valid/runnable without the external pack installed.\n\nFor each of the two occluded bands, replace that link with:\n  AtlasDepthLayerMask.occlusion_mask\n    → INPAINT_ExpandMask (grow ~16–32)\n    → INPAINT_InpaintWithModel (image = original LoadImage output, inpaint_model = INPAINT_LoadInpaintModel loading big-lama.pt)\n    → AtlasCleanPlateLayer.plate_image\n\nThe two occlusion previews to the right show exactly the pixels each pass must fill (bg has the most — everything the ship and mid structure hide; mid only needs what the nearest deck hides).\n\nThe FG layer needs no inpainting — it is wired to the original photo by design, since nothing occludes the frontmost band.\n\nSee INSTALL.md 'Optional Inpaint Integration' for install steps; LanPaint is the optional generative tier for hard disocclusions a LaMa pass smears."
      ]
    },
