        "VIEWPORT CHECKS (Output Desk holds all the buttons — the viewport node itself is render-only):\n\n1. Hit 📽 Project, then dolly/orbit in. Each band is its own ProjectionSource (priority fg 10 > mid 5 > bg 0); clean-plate layers paint head-on AND grazing (facing threshold −1), ordered by depth + priority only.\n2. With the placeholder plates, regions the fg/mid layers uncover repeat original pixels — after wiring the real inpaint chain (note in group ③) they show genuinely clean background instead.\n3. Drop a 🧍 Woman / 🚗 Sedan to sanity-check the metric solve — these load from the vendored three.js r185 bundle (2026-07-07), so they work offline; before the bundle they were silently broken.\n4. Try the Lights tab (💡 two movable point lights, default intensity 0 = no look change) and ☀ exposure — exposure only affects the grey preview, never 📽 Project.\n5. Render Proxy Passes fills the shaded/depth/normal/mask outputs (black until clicked — expected)."
      ]
    }
